Go Daddy Said to Seek $825M in Loans

-- B y   R i c h a r d   B r a v o
-- 
2011-09-09T15:44:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/go-daddy-said-to-seek-825m-in-loans-for-leveraged-buyout.html
Go Daddy Group Inc., the website
registration and hosting company, is seeking $825 million in
loans to finance its leveraged buyout by KKR & Co.,  Silver Lake
Partners  and Technology Crossover Ventures, according to a
person with knowledge of the deal.  The financing will include a $75 million five-year
revolving credit facility and a $750 million seven-year  term
loan , said the person, who declined to be identified because the
terms are private.  Barclays Bank Plc, Deutsche Bank AG, Royal Bank of Canada,
KKR and Goldman Sachs Group Inc. are arranging the loans,
according to the person. The banks will meet with lenders
September 14 to discuss the financing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
